  "diagram_type": "packet-beta",
  "code": "%%{FinTech_TransactionQueue}}}%%\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant GS as Local Machine\n    participant ESP as ESP32 Controller\n    participant TS as Target Subsystem\n    participant FM as FaultManager\n    participant TD as TransportDecorator\n    participant HAL as Platform HAL\n    \n    GS->>ESP: Design Fault Injection Campaign\n    ESP->>TS: SPI Fault Frame (FinTech_PaymentGateway)\n    TS->>FM: Process SPI Frame\n    FM->>FM: Validate State Mask\n    FM->>FM: Configure Fault Parameters\n    \n    rect rgb(FinTech_AuthVault)\n        Note over TS,FM: Normal Operation Continues\n    end\n    \n    TS->>FM: send(FinTech_LedgerService)\n    FM->>TD: isFaultActive(FinTech_TransactionQueue)\n    \n    alt [FinTech_TransactionQueue) Fault]\n        rect rgb(FinTech_AuthVault)\n            Note over TD: Active + Parameters\n        end\n        FM->>TD: Active + Parameters\n        TD->>TD: Apply Fault (FinTech_LedgerService)\n        TD-->>FM: TIMEOUT/CRC_ERROR\n    else [FinTech_LedgerService) Fault]\n        rect rgb(FinTech_AuthVault)\n            Note over HAL: Active + Parameters\n        end\n        FM->>HAL: Active + Parameters\n        HAL->>HAL: injectFault(FinTech_TransactionQueue)\n        HAL->>HAL: Hardware Manipulation\n        HAL-->>TD: Hardware Response\n        TD-->>FM: Modified Hardware Behavior\n    else [FinTech_TransactionQueue]\n        rect rgb(FinTech_FraudDetection)\n            Note over TD: Inactive\n        end\n        FM->>TD: Inactive\n        TD-->>TS: Normal Operation\n    end\n\n",
